1
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:14,640
Let go.

2
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:16,440
If you don't let go, I'll scream.

3
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:17,080
Mr. Zhang.

4
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:18,560
Please give me another chance.

5
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:20,480
I will definitely meet this month's target.

6
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:21,320
Wang Shunshun.

7
00:01:21,320 --> 00:01:23,640
You know the company's current situation.

8
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:25,640
You know how the overall environment is.

9
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:27,560
I really have no choice.

10
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:29,760
I've done my best for the company all these years.

11
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:30,560
You know it.

12
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:31,920
When you told me to do sales,

13
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:33,240
I went out without a word, didn't I?

14
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:33,920
Right?

15
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,960
I handle all internal affairs by myself.

16
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:38,479
I never complain about working overtime.

17
00:01:38,479 --> 00:01:40,600
My daughter is already in ninth grade.

18
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,039
And I've only attended one parent-teacher meeting.

19
00:01:43,039 --> 00:01:46,080
Wang Shunshun, the company needs to survive.

20
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:47,840
The company's evaluation standards

21
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,440
are suffocating me too.

22
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:52,320
These KPIs must be executed from top to bottom.

23
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:53,600
It's the same for me.

24
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,039
I'm under a lot of pressure too.

25
00:01:55,039 --> 00:01:56,200
For the company's performance,

26
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,720
I practically live in the office.

27
00:01:57,720 --> 00:01:59,160
I wake up before the sun

28
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,520
and go to bed late at night.

29
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:01,080
Look.

30
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:02,120
Look at me.

31
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:06,560
Look what happened to me.

32
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,490
Look, Mr. Zhang.

33
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:08,740
Wang Shunshun.

34
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:10,280
What happened to you?

35
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,610
What did the doctor say?

36
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,780
How much time do you have left?

37
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:15,880
It's not that serious.

38
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:18,400
I just stayed up late for the company and lost all my hair.

39
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,400
Look.

40
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,660
My daughter even asks,

41
00:02:21,079 --> 00:02:22,960
Why don't you change your hairstyle after all these years?

42
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:23,840
Look, Mr. Zhang.

43
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:27,600
Wang Shunshun, I understand your situation.

44
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:32,280
But given the company's current state,

45
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:34,040
I really can't help it.

46
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:35,200
If you can't help it, figure something out.

47
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,000
You can't expect us to figure it out.

48
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:37,920
Where am I supposed to figure it out for you?

49
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:38,840
Who is this?

50
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,120
Where did he come from?

51
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,200
Where did this guy come from?

52
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:41,880
Let go first.

53
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:42,520
I won't.

54
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:43,440
No.

55
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:43,800
Bite me?

56
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:44,400
Let go.

57
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:44,880
I just won't.

58
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:46,280
What, you want to bite me?

59
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:49,640
Bullying a woman in broad daylight?

60
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:50,800
How disgraceful!

61
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:51,400
Cut!

62
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:52,680
Cut!

63
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:54,640
Bro.

64
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,720
We are filming.

65
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,360
Small crew, low budget.

66
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:58,960
Don't get too excited.

67
00:02:58,960 --> 00:02:59,890
What's going on?

68
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:02,500
Wait, Director, are we done filming?

69
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:05,880
I thought it was some real drama.

70
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:07,440
So they are just filming.

71
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:08,920
Filming?

72
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:11,640
What does that mean?

73
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:14,240
Are you promoting fundraising to save the nation?

74
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,040
No.

75
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,240
Fundraising?

76
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:18,170
Save the nation?

77
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:18,920
What does that mean?

78
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:21,320
We are filming a contemporary inspirational film,

79
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:22,800
Landing.

80
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:26,050
An inspirational film?

81
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:28,930
What does landing mean?

82
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:30,720
Come.

83
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:31,400
Buddy,

84
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,400
have a cigarette.

85
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,200
I don't smoke. Thank you.

86
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,520
Come.

87
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,450
Look at this guy.

88
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,120
Worked in the industry for over a decade.

89
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,240
In today's environment,

90
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,840
companies face survival crises

91
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,240
and human nature is tested.

92
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,680
It's a huge problem.

93
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,160
And look at this guy.

94
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,840
Once magnificent,

95
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:51,079
graduated from a top university,

96
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:52,760
the pride of his parents,

97
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:53,560
the pillar of his family,

98
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:54,960
a role model for his kids,

99
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,920
and worked diligently for the company.

100
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:58,360
Now in middle age,

101
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,960
he faces an unemployment crisis

102
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:00,720
and has no choice

103
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:02,160
but to wear a wig.

104
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:03,920
This is rat race.

105
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:06,250
He doesn't even have the right to lie flat.

106
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,520
Rat race?

107
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,680
Lie flat?

108
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:11,820
What do these mean?

109
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:14,520
These guys must be together,

110
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:16,050
just doing it for the views.

111
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:17,399
Buddy,

112
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:18,680
say no more,

113
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:20,079
or you'll spoil the plot.

114
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,440
Spoil the plot?

115
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:27,200
His accent doesn't sound local.

116
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,360
Where am I?

117
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,840
Where are my transport truck and supplies?

118
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,100
What unit are you from?

119
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,240
Nanyang Overseas Chinese Mechanic,

120
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,120
Lin Yaozu.

121
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,080
Nanyang...

122
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,850
returned mechanic?

123
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:44,440
On a mission.

124
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:45,240
Yaoyao,

125
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,880
let's go.

126
00:04:47,880 --> 00:04:48,680
Wait a minute.

127
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:51,690
I feel like this guy is a bit different.

128
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:54,560
With this outfit,

129
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,370
you must be an actor too.

130
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,730
Are you from the crew next door?

131
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:00,920
You're really in character.

132
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,520
We are shooting a short drama.

133
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:04,520
It's an inspirational film,

134
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,720
not a war film.

135
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:09,000
Your Republican era accent is a bit out of place.

136
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:10,440
Short drama?

137
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,000
Director, are we shooting?

138
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:14,800
We are losing the light.

139
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:16,520
I have to go home to pick up my daughter.

140
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,400
Shoot.

141
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,400
Everyone, stop staring.

142
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,000
Come on, buddy, come with me.

143
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,480
Let's add WeChat.

144
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,460
When we shoot a war film later,

145
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,440
your vibe

146
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:28,040
will definitely be a hit.

147
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,920
I have an important mission.

148
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,720
What the hell are you guys doing?

149
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,200
What a pity.

150
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:19,720
Assemble!

151
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:29,800
Today,

152
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:32,290
the supplies we are delivering

153
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:34,280
are more important than ever.

154
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:38,140
So we must carefully deliver these supplies to the frontline.

155
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,520
The soldiers on the frontline

156
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:42,800
are waiting for these medicines to save their lives.

157
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:43,530
Understood?

158
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:44,760
Understood.

159
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,850
Get in the truck.

160
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,320
If we don't leave now,

161
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,850
the enemy planes will come.

162
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:10,600
Sit tight.

163
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:12,560
Let's go.

164
00:07:22,280 --> 00:07:23,600
In 1941,

165
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:27,720
the Burma Road was the lifeline connecting China to the outside world during the War of Resistance against Japanese Aggression.

166
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:30,520
It was once the only international transport corridor.

167
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,760
The Nanyang overseas Chinese mechanics

168
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:32,960
left their homes

169
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:34,400
and returned to China from Southeast Asia

170
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:36,640
to drive trucks and transport strategic materials,

171
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:38,480
supporting the frontlines of the war.

172
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:41,920
At this time, Japanese planes wreaked havoc over the Burma Road,

173
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:44,250
dropping deadly bombs one after another.

174
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,480
Grandpa,

175
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,640
if I fail to return,

176
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:43,159
please do not be sad.

177
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:47,780
I would have sacrificed myself for the country,

178
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,880
and I die without regrets.
